fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.config

Class BaseConfig<C extends BaseConfig<C>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.config.BaseConfig<C>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - the "self"-type of this Config
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Config, ImmutableConfig
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BaseBlueprintsConfig, BerkeleyDbConfig, HBaseConfig, InMemoryConfig, MapDbConfig, MongoDbConfig

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public class BaseConfig<C extends BaseConfig<C>>
extends Object
implements Config
    The base Config that creates and manages common configuration that are available for all back-end implementations. It also provides all methods for building and querying a configuration.

    All features are all optional: configuration can be created using all or none of them.

      • BaseConfig

        public BaseConfig()
        Constructs a new BaseConfig with default settings.

        NOTE: This implementation is intended to configure a Store' chain. The created configuration is not associated with any BackendFactory, so it cannot be used to configure a Backend. Use the specific implementation for this.
